# gis-spatial

## Functionality
Geospatial Intelligence (GIS) module that performs Kriging interpolation on environmental measurements at specific geographic coordinates. Renders interpolation results on interactive Leaflet maps with color-coded heatmap layers.

## Tasks
- Accept coordinate input pairs (lat/lng) with associated parameter values
- Execute Kriging spatial interpolation via R `gstat` package (`kriging.R`)
- Render Leaflet.js interactive maps with sample point markers
- Display interpolation grid as a color-scaled overlay
- Show variogram model parameters (nugget, sill, range)
- Display spatial statistics (min, max, mean, standard deviation)
- Support configurable grid density

## Purpose
Environmental pollution is inherently spatial — contamination spreads through water bodies and air masses. This module enables **spatial analysis and visualization** to understand the geographic distribution of pollutants, identify hotspots, and interpolate values at unsampled locations.

## General Roadmap
- Currently `components/GISMap.tsx` (~16KB) for map UI, `kriging.R` for computation
- Depends on `r-sidecar` module for R execution
- Uses `react-leaflet` + `leaflet` for map rendering
- Future: support multiple parameters on the same map
- Future: temporal-spatial analysis (pollution movement over time)

## Key Files
- `components/GISMap.tsx` — Leaflet map component and UI
- `src-tauri/scripts/kriging.R` — Kriging interpolation via R `gstat` + `sp` packages
- `services/analytics.ts` — `KrigingInput`, `KrigingResult`, `KrigingGridPoint` types + `runKriging()` function
